name: Puri Anyar Royal Palace Kerambitan
address: F35M+396, Baturiti, Kerambitan, Tabanan Regency, Bali 82161, Indonesia
review 1:
Here for the community meeting
Beautiful site if the people who are living in it taking care of it more
review 2:
This is the house of the Royal Family of Kerambitan or can be called Puri Anyar Palace. The uniqueness of this  complex lies in its architectural design that makes it different from the houses of common people.

The owner of the palace has given permission to open the palace for foreign tourists for more than three decades. The tourists are offered with cultural performances and attraction. By soing so, the Royal family in Kerambitan has played important role in the preservation of Balinese culture, art and tradition, especially the unique dance of  Okokan which is combined with the classic Calon Arang performance.
review 3: The design and the structures of all buildings are still like originaly from old Hindu kingdom of Majapahit
review 5: Magnificent local palace. This building have been there since 1670s and a lot of famous visitors come by in the past, like david bowie, mick jagger and many others! If you are in Tabanan, make sure to check out!
